GAME DESIGN POSTCARD #15: The 8 Axioms of Convergent Games

What Chess and Go have in common:

1. Perfect information
2. No randomness
3. Irreversible moves
4. Finite state space
5. Forced interaction
6. Structural convergence
7. No dominant strategies
8. Clear termination

Break any axiom, you get a different game. Respect them all, depth emerges.
